flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=275.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wondering...</span><hr size=1> The popular choices are:<br>
<br>
50weap/50dw/28parry - Which gives you all the styles and a decent parry that you can bump up with RAs<br>
<br>
44/44/43 - Sorta considered the 'duelist' spec you'll parry alot but you won't have the 50th styles or the top dmg you can do, but still very viable, esp if you like the parry styles.<br>
<br>
and...<br>
<br>
44/50/3x (i think) -  Trading a little weapons skill and the 50th style for your weapon for more parry while keeping all the DW for the 50th style and of course the chance to swing offhand more.<br>
<br>
As a thruster I would imagine you'll be looking at the 1st choice with alot of Dodger RAs to pull of the really nice evade styles in the thrust line.  But then I'm sure the real thrust mercs could fill you in, in more detail.<br>
<br>
I swing large baby rattles so thats all from just observation.<br>
<br>
-Jawn <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=locnor>LocNor</A> at: 7/3/03 6:14 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#ffffff><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=allnamestakenffs>AllNamesTakenFFS</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Journeyman</span><br>  Posts: 10<br> <font color=#000000>(7/5/03 3:47 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=275.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Wondering...</span><hr size=1> Really nice evade styles? Hrm. Dragonfang is good, the 3-part chain is nothing to write home about.<br>
I'm at 30 with my thrust merc at the moment (sooo painful to solo with thrust compared to my 50 crusher :P) and I'm debating between 44 and 50 thrust. I think 50DW is more or less a given (maximum offhand rate for damage and haste effect, dual shadows, max flurry damage) and that shield isn't worth speccing unless you can take it to 42. If you don't want to pump dodger and lose a lot of potential parry reactionaries whilst trying to land dragonfang, then 44thrust 38parry is probably the sensible option. :] <p>Cheradenine<br>
